            "answer_text": "\u2018shi\u2019 is what translates to death. But beware, \u2018shi\u2019 is also one way to say the number four. This is why there are two ways to say four(shi, and yon). This is also why some larger building may be \u201cmissing\u201d the fourth floor, and that asking for \u2018room four\u2019 or something with four in a hospital setting a taboo, and is not seen as being rude to the dying or as bringing bad luck. shini-masu = dying, verb form/ the act of dying. in different forms you can make this mean different things: Shini-tai = Want of death Shinde-kudasai = Please die ex) inu-wo shinimashita\u2026 = The dog died\u2026 ",
